<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,507,1291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,543,570]" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">Comments.</emphasis>
In his atlas of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pocock" authorityYear="1898" box="[530,676,544,570]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Gnaphosidae</taxonomicName>
of the world, Murphy (2007) introduced the new genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1287,1436,544,570]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1287,1436,544,570]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">Leptodrassex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in order to separate those 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1878" box="[445,594,580,606]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[445,594,580,606]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">Leptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species which did not possess the distinctive character of the latter genus, namely the two large angular retromarginal teeth on their chelicerae (or cheliceral angular lamina, sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Azevedo, G. H. &amp; Griswold, C. E. &amp; Santos, A. J." pageId="10" pageNumber="444" pagination="579 - 626" refId="ref12076" refString="Azevedo, G. H. F, Griswold, C. E. &amp; Santos, A. J. (2018) Systematics and evolution of ground spiders revisited (Araneae, Di- onycha, Gnaphosidae). Cladistics, 34 (6), 579 - 626. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / cla. 12226" type="journal article" year="2018">
Azevedo 
<emphasis box="[151,211,652,678]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">et al.</emphasis>
(2018))
</bibRefCitation>
and instead they had small, conventional teeth on both cheliceral margins. As a result, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1878" box="[151,300,688,714]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,300,688,714]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">Leptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remained to include the type-species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon, 1873)" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1873" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[717,1014,688,714]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femineus">
<emphasis box="[717,846,688,714]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">L. femineus</emphasis>
(Simon, 1873)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Simon, 1914" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1914" box="[1025,1287,688,714]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albidus">
<emphasis box="[1025,1135,688,714]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">L. albidus</emphasis>
Simon, 1914
</taxonomicName>
, and possibly 
<taxonomicName authority="Dalmas, 1919" authorityName="Dalmas" authorityYear="1919" box="[151,431,724,750]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punicus">
<emphasis box="[151,268,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">L. punicus</emphasis>
Dalmas, 1919
</taxonomicName>
(after Murphy 2007), while the rest of eight species still belonging to this genus have not yet been revised after their initial revision and therefore their placement is questioned. Two years later, Levy (2009) further divided the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[429,578,796,822]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[429,578,796,822]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">Leptodrassex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of distinctive differences in the genital organs among its members, thus creating the new genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="2009" box="[475,593,832,858]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[475,593,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">Leptopilos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for those species with a cap-like anterior hood on the female epigyne and “ 
<emphasis box="[164,641,868,894]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">closely grouped laminae on the male palp</emphasis>
”, possibly referring to the multiple tegular apophyses and projections on the male bulb. Thus the species 
<taxonomicName authority="(O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872)" authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1872" baseAuthorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[541,1039,904,930]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenerrimus">
<emphasis box="[541,691,905,930]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">L. tenerrimus</emphasis>
(O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872)
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<typeStatus box="[1084,1132,905,931]" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">type</typeStatus>
species), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dalmas, 1919)" authorityName="Dalmas" authorityYear="1919" baseAuthorityName="Dalmas" baseAuthorityYear="1919" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupa">
<emphasis box="[1243,1328,905,930]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">L. pupa</emphasis>
(Dalmas, 1919)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chatzaki, 2002)" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Chatzaki" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[229,598,940,966]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hadjissaranti">
<emphasis box="[229,405,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">L. hadjissaranti</emphasis>
(Chatzaki, 2002)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chatzaki, 2002)" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Chatzaki" baseAuthorityYear="2002" box="[649,967,940,966]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manolisi">
<emphasis box="[649,773,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">L. manolisi</emphasis>
(Chatzaki, 2002)
</taxonomicName>
were transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="2009" box="[1186,1304,940,966]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1186,1304,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">Leptopilos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in addition to the two newly described 
<taxonomicName authority="Levy, 2009" authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="2009" box="[458,735,976,1003]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levantinus">
<emphasis box="[458,603,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">L. levantinus</emphasis>
Levy, 2009
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Levy, 2009" authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="2009" box="[789,1035,976,1003]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lakhish">
<emphasis box="[789,899,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">L. lakhish</emphasis>
Levy, 2009
</taxonomicName>
. Interestingly, none of these authors mentioned 
<taxonomicName authority="(Spassky, 1940)" authorityName="Spassky" authorityYear="1940" baseAuthorityName="Spassky" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[276,744,1012,1038]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leprodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memorialis">
<emphasis box="[276,560,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">Leprodrassus memorialis</emphasis>
(Spassky, 1940)
</taxonomicName>
which was only transferred to 
<taxonomicName box="[1087,1236,1012,1038]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1087,1236,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">Leptodrassex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Kovblyuk and Nadolny in 2010. It seems that Kovblyuk and Nadolny were not aware of the very recent (at that time) publication by Levy (2009) and had therefore ignored the existence of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levy" authorityYear="2009" box="[848,966,1084,1110]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[848,966,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">Leptopilos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus, to which 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Spassky" baseAuthorityYear="1940" box="[1156,1311,1084,1110]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leprodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="memorialis">
<emphasis box="[1156,1311,1084,1110]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">L. memorialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
apparently belongs, due to the obvious anterior cup on the epigynal anterior margin, very well described and illustrated by the two authors. In this case, the tegular apophyses of the male palps (loosely accepted as a distinctive character even by Levy (2009)) would not justify the transfer from one genus to the other, as they comprise synapomorphic characters within the Leptodrassinae subfamily, recently introduced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Azevedo, G. H. &amp; Griswold, C. E. &amp; Santos, A. J." box="[829,1076,1228,1254]" pageId="10" pageNumber="444" pagination="579 - 626" refId="ref12076" refString="Azevedo, G. H. F, Griswold, C. E. &amp; Santos, A. J. (2018) Systematics and evolution of ground spiders revisited (Araneae, Di- onycha, Gnaphosidae). Cladistics, 34 (6), 579 - 626. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / cla. 12226" type="journal article" year="2018">
Azevedo 
<emphasis box="[935,992,1228,1254]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="444">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
